sub_title: BBA | MSc Student Strategic Management Erasmus
summary:
In 2021, I received my bachelor's degree, cum laude, from Amsterdam School of International Business. 

During this study program I completed a minor in Cross-Cultural Business Skills, have started learning Business Japanese and have participated in various Honours Modules. 
After studying abroad in Japan, I returned to the Netherlands to start my journey at Accenture.

Now I am working part-time at a Dutch startup, helping other students to graduate, while pursuing a Pre-master program at Rotterdam School of Management. I aim to complete the Strategic Management Msc after the preparation phase.

[{'title': 'Creative Director for European Business Skills Magazine ', 'date': {'start': {'month': 10, 'day': None, 'year': 2017}, 'end': {'month': 10, 'day': None, 'year': 2017}}, 'description': 'During a fast-lane autumn school honours course from Amsterdam University of Applied Sciences and Babe»ô-Bolyai University in Cluj Napoca, Romania, we explored the opportunities that lie within the dynamic city of Cluj. The "Emerging Cluj" Magazine was written within three days, with the goal to thoroughly depict Cluj's entrepreneurial prospect while performing under time-pressure and cultural differences. 

As the creative director of the magazine, it was my responsibility to provide that a high-quality magazine would be delivered to properly reflect the vibrancy of Cluj. Responsibilities included leading several teams of visual content creators to deliver in time, designing the magazine inside and out, as well as ensuring that press went smoothly. Given the three-day time limit in which research, writing, and publishing had to be done, these responsibilities allowed me to grow a lot in a short period.
